<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 08 at 7:05PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of heavy snow this evening...
At 7 PM, bands of heavy snow continue to push northward through
Southwest MT. The bands of heavy snow are affecting areas near
West Yellowstone, Ennis and Boulder. This includes portions of
I-15 from Monida to Helena and I-90 from Butte to Bozeman Pass.
Visibility is below a quarter of a mile at times, with snowfall
rates up to an inch per hour.
Expect these bands of heavy snow to continue to move northward
through this region through the rest of the evening.</description>
